<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE recipe SYSTEM "../recipes.dtd">
<recipe>
	<title>Key Lime Pie</title>
	<meta>
		<dishtype>Pies</dishtype>
	</meta>
	<group>
		<label>Crust</label>
		<ingredients>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
                    <value>1 1/4</value>
                    <unit>cup</unit>
                    <!--
                    <altmeasure>
                        <value>@@</value>
                        <unit>oz</unit>
                    </altmeasure>
                    -->
				</quantity>
				<item>graham cracker crumbs</item>
			</ingredient>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>5</value>
					<unit>tbs</unit>
				</quantity>
				<item>sugar</item>
			</ingredient>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>5</value>
					<unit>tbs</unit>
				</quantity>
				<item>butter</item>
			</ingredient>
		</ingredients>
		<steps>
			<step>Preheat the oven to <temperature>350</temperature>.</step>
			<step>If using whole graham crackers, pulse them in a food processor until evenly sandy. Mix together graham cracker crumbs and sugar.</step>
			<step>Melt butter and stir together graham cracker crumbs until butter is evenly distributed.</step>
			<step>Grease a <equipment>9-inch pie plate</equipment>. Spread crumbs on bottom and sides evenly and press down.</step>
			<step>Bake about <time>10 minutes</time> until lightly browned. Cool before adding filling. Keep oven on.</step>
		</steps>
	</group>
	<group>
		<label>Filling</label>
		<ingredients>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>1</value>
                    <unit>can</unit>
					<altmeasure>
                        <quantity>
                            <value>14</value>
                            <unit>oz</unit>
                        </quantity>
                    </altmeasure>
				</quantity>
				<item>sweetened condensed milk</item>
			</ingredient>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>3</value>
				</quantity>
				<item>egg yolks</item>
			</ingredient>
			<ingredient mainingredient="true">
				<quantity>
					<value>2/3</value>
					<unit>cup</unit>
				</quantity>
				<item>key lime juice</item>
			</ingredient>
            <ingredient optional="true">
                <quantity>
                    <value>2</value>
                    <unit>tsp</unit>
                </quantity>
                <item>key lime zest</item>
            </ingredient>
		</ingredients>
		<steps>
			<step>Beat together the condensed milk and egg yolks together until smooth.</step>
			<step>Stir in the lime juice and zest until evenly mixed.</step>
			<step>Pour filling over the baked crust.</step>
			<step>Return to oven and bake until edges are firm and center is still slightly wobbly, about <time>15 minutes</time>.</step>
			<step>Cool on a rack. Cover and chill until firm.</step>
		</steps>
	</group>
    <group>
        <label>Topping</label>
        <ingredients>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>1/2</value>
					<unit>cup</unit>
				</quantity>
				<item>whipping cream</item>
			</ingredient>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>1</value>
					<unit>tsp</unit>
				</quantity>
				<item>key lime juice</item>
			</ingredient>
			<ingredient>
				<quantity>
					<value>1</value>
					<unit>tbs</unit>
				</quantity>
				<item>sugar</item>
			</ingredient>
        </ingredients>
        <steps>
            <step>Combine ingredients and <procedure>whip</procedure> until stiff.</step>
            <step>Transfer to a small <equipment>pastry bag</equipment> fitted with a <equipment>star tip</equipment>. <procedure>Pipe</procedure> 12 decorative dots in a circle around the outer part the pie.</step>
        </steps>
    </group>
</recipe>
